  "text": "Session key rotation concurrency analysis for Django session framework:\n\n1. CYCLE_KEY ENTRY POINT (django/contrib/sessions/backends/base.py, SessionBase.cycle_key, lines 428-437):\n   - Called during login to rotate session keys for security\n   - Calls self.create() to generate and persist a new session key\n   - Preserves current session data across the key rotation\n\n2. NEW SESSION KEY GENERATION (django/contrib/sessions/backends/base.py, SessionBase._get_new_session_key, lines 194-199):\n   - Base class method that generates candidate session keys\n   - Uses get_random_string(32, VALID_KEY_CHARS) to generate random 32-character keys\n   - Checks if key exists via self.exists() before returning\n   - RACE CONDITION: exists() check is NOT atomic with subsequent INSERT\n\n3. DATABASE BACKEND CREATE (django/contrib/sessions/backends/db.py, SessionStore.create, lines 68-79):\n   - Wraps key generation and persistence in a retry loop\n   - Calls _get_new_session_key() then save(must_create=True)\n   - On CreateError (collision detected), retries with a new key\n   - COLLISION HANDLING: YES - explicit retry mechanism on collision\n\n4. DATABASE BACKEND SAVE (django/contrib/sessions/backends/db.py, SessionStore.save, lines 114-137):\n   - Performs actual database INSERT/UPDATE via Django ORM save()\n   - When must_create=True, uses force_insert=True (line 128)\n   - COLLISION DETECTION: Catches IntegrityError and raises CreateError when must_create=True (lines 130-132)\n   - This prevents silent overwrites - the parent create() loop retries instead\n\n5. PRIMARY KEY CONSTRAINT (django/contrib/sessions/base_session.py, AbstractBaseSession, line 28):\n   - session_key is defined as primary_key=True\n   - Enforces database-level unique constraint on session keys\n   - Guarantees IntegrityError on duplicate INSERT attempts\n\nCONCURRENCY SAFETY SUMMARY:\n- COLLISION HANDLING EXISTS: The create() method explicitly handles key collisions by retrying with a new key (lines 75-77 in db.py)\n- RACE CONDITION PRESENT: Between the exists() check in _get_new_session_key() (base.py line 198) and database INSERT, another request could create the same key\n- GRACEFUL RECOVERY: The race condition is handled by catching IntegrityError in save() and raising CreateError, triggering a retry in create()\n- NO SILENT OVERWRITES: The force_insert=True parameter and IntegrityError handling prevent silently overwriting existing sessions\n- GUARANTEED PERSISTENCE: The database primary key constraint ensures only one session can exist per key"
}

